{"descriptions":[{"id":1409,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn Literary Tibetan, verb stems are often inflected according to the three tenses and the imperative mood: a maximum of \u003cem\u003efour forms.\u003c/em\u003e These are traditionally referred to as \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུས་ད་ལྟ་བ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;present,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུས་མ་འོངས་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;future,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུས་འདས་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;past\u0026rdquo; and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐུལ་ཚིག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;imperative.\u0026rdquo; In Literary Tibetan, not all verbs have four forms; some are either invariable or have only two or three forms.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eI generally use the traditional terminology for the three tenses: past, present, and future. However it is more accurate to speak of aspects (or tense-aspect). The present \u0026ldquo;tense\u0026rdquo; is an imperfective aspect, since it may in fact be used not only in the present but also in the imperfective past. For example, in the following sentence:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཅུང་དགའ་བོ་རབ་བྱུང་ཡང་བསླངས་པ་ལ་མི་སློབ།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Though Nanda became a monk, he wouldn\u0026rsquo;t learn the precepts.\u0026rdquo; (Literally: \u0026ldquo;...he does not learn the precepts.\u0026rdquo;)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eAlthough the verb stem \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསློབ་\u003c/span\u003e is in the \u0026ldquo;present\u0026rdquo; (and not the past \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསླངས་\u003c/span\u003e), it conveys the meaning of the imperfective \u003cstrong\u003epast\u003c/strong\u003e. Note also the use of the imperfective negation \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམི་\u003c/span\u003e (and not the \u0026ldquo;past\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe traditional designation \u0026ldquo;past\u0026rdquo; is technically speaking as inappropriate as \u0026ldquo;present.\u0026rdquo; What we are actually dealing with is the perfective aspect: this \u0026ldquo;past\u0026rdquo; tense is in fact also used for the perfective future. For example in the sentence:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཅུང་དགའ་བོ་ལྷ་ཡུལ་དུ་སྐྱེས་ནས་བདེ་བ་མྱོངས་ཏེ།\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགེ་འབྲས་ཟད་པ་དང་འདིར་སྐྱེ་བ་ཡིན།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Nanda\u003cem\u003e will be born\u003c/em\u003e in paradise and will enjoy happiness, (then) when his merit runs out, he will be reborn here.\u0026rdquo; (Literally: \u0026ldquo;Once he has been born in the divine realms and has enjoyed happiness....\u0026rdquo;)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn the first clause, the verb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐྱེས་\u003c/span\u003e is in the \u0026ldquo;past\u0026rdquo; (and not the future \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐྱེ་\u003c/span\u003e) but it denotes a perfective \u003cem\u003efuture\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIt should be remembered that the number of distinct verb stems has been considerably reduced in the spoken language, and the role of inflection has been largely supplanted by auxiliary verbs. Furthermore, the majority of verbs in the spoken language consist of an invariable noun and a verbalizer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThere are two main reasons for the reduction in the number of inflections in Spoken Tibetan:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1.) Certain forms have either become outmoded or completely obsolete.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e2.) There is a high degree of homophony. In the course of the phonological evolution of Central Tibetan, many verbs with different prefixes (or suffixes, etc.) have come to be pronounced identically. The distinctions that have been retained in writing have disappeared in the spoken language.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe table below provides several examples of comparisons between written and colloquial forms. The first line (in italics) below the Tibetan presents the spelling (and therefore the archaic pronunciation), while the second shows the THDL simplified phonetic pronunciation. There are also some examples (in parenthesis) of the literary pronunciation, but these have generally lost their currency in the spoken language.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePresent-future\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePast\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eImperative\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐོར་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསྐོར་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eskor \u003c/em\u003e/ \u003cem\u003ebskor\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ekor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསྐོར་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebskor\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ekor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐོར་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eskor\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ekor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To turn\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཏོང་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཏང་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003egtong \u003c/em\u003e/ \u003cem\u003egtang\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(tong)   tang\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཏང་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebtang\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003etang\u003cem\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐོངས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ethongs\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(tong)   tang\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To send\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའགོག་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགག་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u0026rsquo;gog\u003c/em\u003e / \u003cem\u003edgag\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(gok) gak\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀག་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebkag\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ekak\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁོག་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ekhog\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(khok) gak\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To stop\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའཆོར་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u0026rsquo;chor\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(chor) shor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཤོར་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eshor\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eshor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026Oslash;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To escape\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཟོ་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཟོ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ezo\u003c/em\u003e / \u003cem\u003ebzo\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ezo\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཟོས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebzos\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ez\u0026ouml;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཟོས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebzos\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ez\u0026ouml;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To make\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebyed \u003c/em\u003e/ \u003cem\u003ebya\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ej\u0026eacute;/ ja\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebyas\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ej\u0026eacute;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱོས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebyos\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(j\u0026ouml;) j\u0026eacute;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To do\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྒྱག་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབརྒྱག་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ergyag \u003c/em\u003e/ \u003cem\u003ebrgyag\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003egyak\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབརྒྱབ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebrgyab\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003egyap\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྒྱོབ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ergyob\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003egyop / gyap\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To construct\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལྟ་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབལྟ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003elta\u003c/em\u003e / \u003cem\u003eblta\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eta\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབལྟས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebltas\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003et\u0026eacute;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལྟོས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eltos\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003et\u0026ouml;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To look\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཟ་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཟའ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eza\u003c/em\u003e / \u003cem\u003ebza\u0026lsquo;\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eza\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཟས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ebzas\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ez\u0026eacute;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཟོ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ezo\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ezo\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To eat\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའབུལ་\u003c/span\u003e / \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདབུལ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u0026rsquo;bul\u003c/em\u003e / \u003cem\u003edbul\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eb\u0026uuml;l / \u0026uuml;l\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕུལ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ephul\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ep\u0026uuml;l\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕུལ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ephul\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ep\u0026uuml;l\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"115\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u0026ldquo;To offer\u0026rdquo; (H)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe disappearance of certain verb forms in the oral register and the fact that there are so many homophones present certain problems when writing in a conversational or vernacular\u0026mdash;rather than a literary\u0026mdash;style. The tense of a given form may be radically different in oral and Literary Tibetan. Verb stems corresponding to the literary past tense are used for the present-future in the oral register (since this is the only form that is used in speech, e.g., \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཀག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;to stop\u0026rdquo;). Correspondence between literary and oral forms is a complex matter. In the case of modern texts of this kind, readers should take care to identify the tense of the verb from the auxiliaries \u003cem\u003eand not from the inflection\u003c/em\u003e of the main verb.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eOn the other hand, Literary Tibetan contains a large number of \u0026ldquo;causative/resultative\u0026rdquo; verb pairs. Compared to the basic resultative stem, the causative has always an additional argument corresponding to an intentional agent performing the action. All the causative verbs are transitive and volitional, while resultative verbs are usually intransitive and non-volitional. When occurring in the same sentence, the causative form points to the effort of the agent, whereas the resultative form essentially shows the result of the action (xxlink MST 35.3). In written Tibetan, the causative verb often carries a superscript \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eས\u003c/span\u003e. In the spoken language, causatives are often distinguishable from their resultative form by tone and aspiration, but in many cases this opposition, too, has disappeared.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCausative\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eResultative\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐོར་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To turn\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ekor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའཁོར་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To circulate\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003ekhor\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཅག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To break\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003echak\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be broken\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003echak\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསྒྲིགས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To arrange\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003edrik\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའགྲིག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be arranged,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to be enough\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003edrik\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབསྒུལ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To cause to move\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eg\u0026uuml;l\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd width=\"192\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའགུལ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To move,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to be moved\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eg\u0026uuml;l\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:50 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:50 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}